ond is 127 × 60=7,620\n\nThird is 127 ×9=1,143\n\nSo total product is 88,900 +7,620 +1,143.\n\nLet me compute 88,900 +7,620 first. 88,900 + 7,000 is 95,900; plus 620: 95,900 +620=96,520.\n\nThen add 1,143: 96,520 +1,143.\n\n96,520 + 1,000=97,520; plus 143 is 97,520 +143=97,663.\n\nTherefore, 88,900 +7,620 +1,143 = 97,663? Wait wait wait let me verify the additions step.\n\nWait let me recast this.\n\nWait 88,900 +7,620= 96,520\n\n96,520 +1,143=?\n\nCalculate 96,520 + 1,000=97,520\n\n97,520 +143=97,663.\n\nTherefore the total is 97,663?\n\nWait, but let me cross-verify this with the initial multiplication.\n\nWait to double-check, maybe I should compute using another method.\n\nAlternative method:\n\nCompute 127 × 769:\n\nI can break 769 into 700 + 60 +9.\n\n127 ×700 = 88,900 (same as before)\n\n127 ×60= let me recalculate:\n\n127 × 60=127×6×10= 762×10=7,620.\n\n127 ×9: 1,143 same.\n\nAdding together: 88,900 +7,620=96,520; +1,143=97,663. So same result. Hmm that seems correct.\n\nWait let me confirm using another strategy.\n\nCompute 769 ×127:\n\nLet me use the standard multiplication:\n\n127\n\nx769\n\nMultiply 127 ×9, then 127 ×60, then 127 ×700, summing.\n\nWait same as before.\n\nBut maybe cross verify using (120 +7)(700 +60 +9), but maybe adding parts.\n\nBut since two different breakdowns gave me 97,663, let me confirm:\n\nCompute step by step.\n\nCompute 127 ×700: Well, yes 127 × 700= (127 ×7) ×100= 889 ×100=88,900.\n\n127 ×60: 127 ×6 ×10=762 ×10=7,620\n\n127 ×9=1,143\n\nAdding: 88,900 +7,620= 96,520; +1,143= total 96,520+1,143=97,663.\n\nAlternatively, can we verify this through another method?\n\nLet me use the standard multiplication algorithm.\n\nCompute 127 * 769:\n\nBreak 769 into 700 + 60 +9.\n\nSo calculate:\n\nFirst, compute 127 * 700: 127*7*100= (889)*100=88,900\n\nThen, 127*60.\n\n127*60: compute 127*6*10= 762*10=7,620\n\nThen, 127*9=1,143\n\nSum all three results: 88,900 +7,620 +1,143.\n\nCalculate 88,900 +7,620: 88,900 +7,000=95,900; 95,900 +620=96,520.\n\nThen 96,520 +1,143:\n\n96,520 + 1,000=97,520\n\n97,520 +143=97,663\n\nYes, same result again.\n\nLet me check it with another approach for further confirmation.\n\nLet me multiply 127 × 769 using long method.\n\nFirst multiply 127×9:\n\n 127\n× 769\n\nWait no, let me write it properly.\n\nWait 769 × 127.\n\nMultiply 769 × 100 =76,900\n\nThen 769 ×20=15,380\n\nThen 769 ×7=5,383\n\nWait let me express 127 as 100 +20 +7. Then total product:\n\nWait no, let me just use the standard multiplication:\n\nBreakdown 127 ×769.\n\nLet me note:\n\n769 x"], label: None, reward: {'reward': -1.0, 'accuracy': 0, 'format_score': 0}
