et me recount.\n\nWait,\n\nWait 713 = 700 + 13, so 625*700 is indeed 437,500. Correct because 625*7 is 4375 and followed by two zeros, yes.\n\n625*13: Let's double-check:\n\n13×625:\n\nCalculate 10 ×625 = 6250\n\n3 ×625= 1875\n\nSo 6250 +1875= 8125, yes. So that is 8125, so adding 437,500 +8,125= 445,625. But wait adding 437,500 and 8,125:\n\n437,500 + 8,125 is counting.\n\n437,500 + 8,000 is 445,500\n\nThen +125 is 445,625. Yes, correct.\n\nSo 625×713=445,625. Hmm.\n\nBut let me cross-verify by multiplying directly.\n\nLet me think of 625×713.\n\nAnother way is to note that 625 is 5^4, or it's 625 = 5^4 = 625 but maybe we can express 713*625 as 713*(5^4)=713*625.\n\nLet me compute 713 ×625:\n\nHmm, 625 is 5/8 of 1000? Wait perhaps breaking it down:\n\n625 = 600 + 25\n\nSo 713 ×600 = 713*6*100\n\nWait 713*600: 713*6=4278, so 4278*100=427,800\n\n713*25\n\n25 is 1/4 of 100. So 713*25 is (713*100)/4, let's see 713*100=71,300; divide by4: 71300 / 4=17,825.\n\nTherefore total should be 427,800 +17,825 =445,625 same as before.\n\nYes, so 713×625 is 445,625, therefore the product is indeed 445,625.\n\nTherefore the final answer is 445,625.\n\nWait let me just confirm with another approach in case any mistake was there.\n\nCompute 713 × 625:\n\nLet's think, 700×625 + 13×625\n\n700×625: 625×700= 437,500\n\n13×625: as earlier is 8,125 thus sum is 437,500 + 8,125= 445,625. Yes same result.\n\nSo indeed 445,625 is correct.\n\nTherefore, I think the product is 445,625. Hence enclosed in box as per instruction.\n\nWait wait hold, let me just ensure:\n\nMultiply 625 ×713:\n\nCompute 625 *700 = 437,500\n\n625*13 is 8,125\n\nTotal=437,500 +8,125= 445,625\n\nYes.\n\nAlternatively using standard multiplication:\n\n625  \nx713\n/ let's do standard multiplication:\n\nMultiply 625 × 3 = 1,875  \nMultiply 625 ×10=  6250? Wait, perhaps more precise:\n\nWait:\n\nLet's set it up:\n\n    625\n  x713\n  ----\nMultiply 625 by 3, units place:\n\n625 × 3 = 1,875\n\nMultiply 625 × 10, which is 6,250 shifted one position:\n\nWait wait no, according to standard multiplication:\n\n      625\n    × 713\n    --------\n\nWe can do it as:\n\nMultiply 625 by 3 (units digit of 713): 625 ×3 =1,875\n\nMultiply 625 by1 (tens place of713): 625 ×10 =6,250\n\nMultiply 625 by 7 (hundreds place of713): 625 ×700= 437,500\n\nSo sum all together:\n\n1,875\n\n+6,250 (shift one position:  6,250, but written next to 1,875 shifted one decimal would make it  +6,250 *10= 62,500 ?? Wait perhaps better method other way.\n\nWait let me break down:\n\nThe number 713 is 7×100 +1×10 +3×1.\n\nTherefore,\n\n    625 ×700 +625×10 +625×3.\n\nWhich is:\n\n625×700=437,500\n\n625×10=6,250\n\n625×3=1,875\n\nTotal sum:\n\n437,500 + 6,250= 443,750\n\n443,750 +1,8"], label: None, reward: {'reward': -1.0, 'accuracy': 0, 'format_score': 0}
