ait let me confirm using step by step, to make sure I didn't make any error.\n\nLet me redo an alternative calculation.\n\nCompute 158*746:\n\nFirst compute 746*100=74,600; Wait wait 158*700=110,600\n\nWait, it's better to compute 746*158:\n\nBreakdown 746*158:\n\nCompute 746*100=74,600\n\n746*50=37,300 (because 746*50 is half of 746*100 and times 2?) Wait no:746*50= (700*50)+(46*50)=35,000 +2,300=37,300\n\n746*8= 5,968\n\nSo total 746*158= (746*100)+(746*50)+(746*8)=74,600 +37,300 +5,968=(74,600+37,300)=111,900 +5,968=117,868\n\nTherefore 746*158=117,868\n\nSubtract from numerator:117,973 -117,868=105.\n\nTherefore 117,973=158*746 +105, so\n\n117973 divided by158 is 746 with remainder105. Therefore integer division is746.\n\nTherefore the integer part, which is the quotient is 746.\n\nBut just to make sure let's verify with another approach.\n\nAlternatively I can use another way:\n\nFind 158*700=110600\n\n117973 minus that= 117973 -110600=7373\n\nCompute 7373 /158 let's find how many times\n\n158*40=6"], label: None, reward: {'reward': -1.0, 'accuracy': 0, 'format_score': 0}
