ng division approach.\n\nWe can divide step by step.\n\nCompute how many times 489 goes into 103011.\n\nFirst, see how many digits there are: 5 or 6?\n\nIt might take too long.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps it's better using the approximate method.\n\nEstimate 489*200 is 97800. 1000 - 489 is 511 something.\n\nCompute how many times 489*2 is 978, difference towards 103011.\n\nWait maybe a better approach. Let's calculate it as:\n\nLet me write 103011 ÷489.\n\nHow many times 489 into 1030.\n\nCompute 489*2 = 978,  subtract: 1030 -978=52 So 2... remainder 52.\n\nBring down 11: 521\n\n489 goes into 521 once.\n\nSo total quotient so far after first part is 21, because we did two steps:\n\nWrite down 21... Wait wait this needs step-by-step performing long division properly.\n\nWait let me rewrite:\n\nDivide 103011 by 489:\n\nFirst, 489 into 1030 (first four digits): 1030 divided by 489: 2 times, because 489*2=978, which subtracted is 1030-978=52. Bring down 1, making it 521.\n\nNow, 521 divided by 489 is 1 time.\n\nSo multiply 1 and bring down 1: Wait no, wait.\n\nWait the full dividend is 103011:\n\nStart by writing:\n\n489 ) 103011\n\nFirst, 489 into 1030: 2 times.\n\n2*489=978\n\n1030 -978 =52\n\nBring down 1: 521\n\n489 into 521: 1 time.\n\n1*489=489\n\nSubtract 521-489=32\n\nBring down 1: making it 321\n\n489 into 321 is 0 times, so next digit 0.\n\nMultiply 0*489=0\n\nSubtract: 321-0=321\n\nRemaining digits: bring down next, but since the number is done, value is 321.\n\nSo total quotient: first 2, then 1, then 0, and remainder 321.\n\nSo putting it together: quotient is 21 at ten thousands... Wait, let me be precise.\n\nWait let me do digit by digit:\n\nDivide 103011 ÷489:\n\nHow many times 489 fits into 1030? As I found 2.\n\nSubtract, bring down next digit: 521.\n\n489 into 521 is 1 time, so next digit 1.\n\nSubtract 489 from 521=32.\n\nBring down the next digit:1, so now 321.\n\n489 doesn't go into 321, bring down the next 1? Wait no, the number 103011 is last digit